note.body:
It is somewhat weird to use a lib that forces locations onto METAR weather stations, then to use a provider for weather data that provides data for a fine grid and not only the METEAR weather stations, and then replacing that with another paid service that uses the original provider… and still retain the original lib that created the problem with lock-in to the METAR weather stations.

target_title: a lot of location in Switzerland missing

note.body:
I see, this is indeed a hard task. 
Just do some research without konowing your requirements, this looks interesting:

https://github.com/open-meteo/open-meteo

Or just use another approach for this problem:

implement a web scraper which scrapes the city the user wishes to get the weather from.
This way, you not need any api, but have to ensure there are a good list of weather sites and also the scraper is working. E.g after some changes to websites.
You also completely free and not dependent on any libgweather? Also have more free time to do other stuff!
